               <note>
                  <date type="foundation" notBefore="1400" notAfter="1500">1400-1500</date>
                  <desc type="foundation">Local tradition tells that the church was built in the Aksumite time, under <persName ref="PRS3729ellaAm">King ʿAlāmedā</persName>, but re-established by <persName ref="PRS4327GabraMa">Gabra Masqal</persName>.</desc>
                  <ab type="history">Dabr. An intact old structure (possibly the old church) stands in the compound, in front of the recent church. &#xD;
Aksumite pillars are used in the recent church building. &#xD;
Some old wooden parts are preserved in the treasury.&#xD;
A burial place, possibly old, can be seen behind the church.  &#xD;</ab>
                  <ab type="tabot"><measure quantity="22"/>Tābots (22): those remembered are <persName ref="PRS6819Mary" type="tabot">Mary</persName>, <persName ref="PRS3249Cyriacus" type="tabot">Qirqos</persName>, 
                     <persName ref="PRS1906Ananyao" type="tabot">ʾAnānyā</persName>, <persName ref="PRS7049Michael" type="tabot">Michael</persName>, 
                     <persName ref="PRS9162TaklaHa" type="tabot">Takla Haymanot</persName>, 2 of <persName ref="PRS10581Zamika" type="tabot">ʾAragāwi</persName>,&#xD;
                     <persName ref="PRS12016Evangelists#Four" type="tabot">Four Living Creatures</persName>, 
                     <persName ref="PRS4306GabraMa" type="tabot">Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</persName>, <ref type="authFile" corresp="TrueCross">Holy Cross</ref>.</ab>
                  <ab type="description">8 Mss. photographed: <ref type="mss" corresp="ESwq001">WQ-001</ref> “The Rite of the Holy Week”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESwq002">WQ-002</ref> “Homily on the Sabbath of Christians”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESwq003">WQ-003</ref> “Book of the Funeral Rite”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESwq004">WQ-004</ref> “Story of St. Mary”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESwq005">WQ-005</ref> “Missal”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESwq006">WQ-006</ref> “Vita of Cyriacus”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESwq007">WQ-007</ref> “Four Gospels”; <ref type="mss" corresp="ESwq008">WQ-008</ref> “Miracles of Jesus”.</ab>
  
